1. Download & Install Etcd:

Download the Etcd RPM package for your system from the official repository:  
http://ftp.postgresql.org/pub/repos/yum/common/pgdg-rhel9-extras/redhat/rhel-9-x86_64/

Install the package:
sudo rpm -ivh etcd-*.rpm

2. Configure, Start & Verify Etcd:

Go to the configuration directory and edit etcd.conf according to your cluster setup (node name, initial cluster members, listen URLs, etc.). Then start and verify the cluster:
cd /etc/etcd
# Edit etcd.conf here

sudo systemctl enable etcd
sudo systemctl start etcd

3.Verify cluster status:

source etcd-env.sh
etcdctl endpoint status --write-out=table --endpoints=$ENDPOINTS

